message.content: cs.CR, cs.IOT, cs.CYBER, cs.SE, cs.SY - The paper discusses the challenges of providing security for intermittently powered computational IoT devices, which falls under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CR) and IoT (cs.IOT). The paper also discusses the construction and evaluation of a basic hash primitive, which falls under the category of cryptography (cs.CYBER) and software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper outlines an execution model for these primitives under intermittent powering, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
